OL,3,CNuclear veteran who had 'no
OL,4,Cprotection' at atom bomb trials calls
OL,5,Cfor inquiry
OL,7,FJohn Taylor, who is 87 and known as
OL,8,F'Jack', was only in his early twenties
OL,9,Fwhen he was deployed to Australia in
OL,10,F1957 to work at an airbase. Little did
OL,11,Fhe know, he would witness three atom
OL,12,Fbomb explosions as part of Cold War
OL,13,Fnuclear trials later that year.
OL,15,FJack, who lives in South Shields, said
OL,16,Fhe lived in a two man tent during the
OL,17,Foperation and when the day of the
OL,18,Ffirst bomb test finally came, he had
OL,19,F"no protection" from radiation or
OL,20,Fcontamination.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/10
